snippet: The President has given orders to the Naval stations to fire salutes and extend all military honors to Kossuth, at New-York, and all other places. A grand dinner will be given him at the President's house....
lead_paragraph: The President has given orders to the Naval stations to fire salutes and extend all military honors to Kossuth, at New-York, and all other places. A grand dinner will be given him at the President's house.

headline.main: LATEST INTELLIGENCE; By Telegraph to The New-York Times. From Washington,--Kossuth's Reception.--Recall of Consul Owen.--Virginia Election, &c.
